      "body" : "```suggestion\r\n    if ((!jVal.read(std::string(\"[\")+strVal+std::string(\"]\")) &&\r\n        !jVal.read(std::string(\"[\\\"\")+strVal+std::string(\"\\\"]\"))) ||\r\n```\r\nJust as an idea, feel free to ignore :)\r\nThis would be shorter, requires no additional methods and also does the job (except for `getblockstats \"'<blockhash>'\"`). But - and that could be more important - it keeps the error message if the blockhash is e.g. too long (`hash_or_height must be of length 64 (not 66, for ...`), while your solution throws an JSON parsing error which could be misleading for a user ð¤ ",
